<subSubSection id="1BE001ABFFB1662FE6F9AB7AFAF7820C" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="53455220FFB1662CE6F9AB7AFCB486EE" blockId="5.[136,1452,1281,2063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Note. 
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB1662CE745AB7AFDF58675" author="Galland, N. &amp; Favarger, C." box="[257,559,1569,1596]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="231 - 235" refId="ref5943" refString="Galland, N. &amp; Favarger, C. (1985) Notes de taxonomie et de nomenclature sur la flore orophile du Maroc. Candollea 40 (1): 231 - 235. https: // doi. org / 10.5169 / seals- 879783" type="journal article" year="1985">Galland &amp; Favarger (1985)</bibRefCitation>
recognized three varieties in 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE530AB7AFB858672" authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1873" box="[884,1119,1569,1595]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conringioides">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE530AB7AFB858672" box="[884,1119,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Arabis conringioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, including var. 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE34EAB7AFED58616" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="conringioides" variety="werneri">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE34EAB7AFA7E8672" box="[1290,1444,1569,1595]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">conringioides</emphasis>
, var. 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE6FCAB1DFED58616" box="[184,271,1606,1631]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">werneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE708AB1EFD5D8616" authority="Maire. The" authorityName="Maire. The" box="[332,647,1605,1631]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" rank="variety" variety="aphanostyla">
var. 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE738AB1EFDDF8616" box="[380,517,1605,1631]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">aphanostyla</emphasis>
Maire. The
</taxonomicName>
last was invalidly published in 
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB1662CE5ACAB1EFBA58629" author="Maire, R." box="[1000,1151,1605,1632]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref7888" refString="Maire, R. (1967) Flore de l'Afrique du Nord 13. Paul Lechevalier, Paris, 365 pp." type="book" year="1967">Maire (1967)</bibRefCitation>
. By contrast, 
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB1662CE353AB1EFEFF86CA" author="Dobignard, A. &amp; Jordan, D." pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="67 - 104" refId="ref5664" refString="Dobignard, A. &amp; Jordan, D. (1987) Nouvelles observations sur la flore du Maroc. 1. Contribution a l'etude de la flore du Haut-Atlas. Saussurea 18: 67 - 104." type="journal article" year="1987">
Dobignard &amp; 
<collectingCountry id="2BED12B0FFB1662CE6CCAB32FF0986CA" box="[136,211,1641,1667]" name="Jordan" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Jordan</collectingCountry>
(1987)
</bibRefCitation>
recognized the two subspecies listed here, though they accepted 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE247AB32FB6786CA" box="[1027,1213,1641,1667]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" rank="variety" variety="aphanostyla">
var. 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE270AB32FB6786CA" box="[1076,1213,1641,1667]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">aphanostyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which 
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB1662CE35CAB32FF2C86EE" author="Dobignard, A. &amp; Chatelain, C. &amp; Fischer, M. &amp; Orso, J. &amp; Jeanmonod, D." pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="ref5702" refString="Dobignard, A., Chatelain, C., Fischer, M., Orso, J. &amp; Jeanmonod, D. (2011) Index synonymique de la flore d'Afrique du Nord 3, Dicotyledoneae: Balsaminaceae-Euphorbiaceae. Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques de la Ville de Geneve, Geneve, 449 pp." type="book" year="2011">
Dobignard 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE3D3AB31FF7F86EE" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
subsequently reduced to synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE4E8ABD6FCBD86EE" authorityName="Dobignard &amp; Jordan" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Quezel" box="[684,871,1677,1703]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="conringioides" subSpecies="humbertii">
subsp. 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE4BEABD6FCBD86EE" box="[762,871,1677,1703]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">humbertii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="53455220FFB1662CE6F9ABEBFCD587EA" blockId="5.[136,1452,1281,2063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE6F9ABEBFBB48682" authority="(Jahand. &amp; Maire) Al-Shehbaz, M. Koch, R. Karl, &amp; D. A. German" authorityName="Al-Shehbaz, M. Koch, R. Karl, &amp; D. A. German" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Al-Shehbaz, M. Koch, R. Karl, &amp; D. A. German" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[189,1134,1712,1740]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hurkaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="josiae" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE6F9ABEBFEB58682" bold="true" box="[189,367,1712,1739]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Hurkaea josiae</emphasis>
(Jahand. &amp; Maire) Al-Shehbaz, M. Koch, R. Karl, &amp; D.A. German
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE23EABEBFB2C8682" bold="true" box="[1146,1270,1712,1739]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="7ABD3349FFB1662CE23EABEBFB2C8682" box="[1146,1270,1712,1739]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
≡ 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE352ABEAFE0586B9" authority="Jahandiez &amp; Maire (1923: 66)" authorityName="Jahandiez &amp; Maire" authorityPageNumber="66" authorityYear="1923" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="josiae">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE352ABEAFA718682" box="[1302,1451,1713,1739]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Arabis josiae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB1662CE6CCAB8EFE0586B9" author="Jahandiez, E. &amp; Maire, R." box="[136,479,1749,1776]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="65 - 73" refId="ref6324" refString="Jahandiez, E. &amp; Maire, R. (1923) Plantae maroccanae novae. Bulletin de la Societe d'histoire naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord 14 (2): 65 - 73." type="journal article" year="1923">Jahandiez &amp; Maire (1923: 66)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<typeStatus id="8C41EC82FFB1662CE7ADAB8EFDFB86A6" box="[489,545,1749,1775]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Type</typeStatus>
indication: “Hab. in silvis (quercetis et cedretis) Atlantis Medii maroccani supra oppidum Azrou, ubi maio floret – 
<typeStatus id="8C41EC82FFB1662CE44BABA2FD89875A" box="[527,595,1785,1811]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Typus</typeStatus>
in Herbario Universitatis Algeriensis. … Cette plante a été ensuite récoltée en fleurs, le 
<date id="274474E0FFB1662CE756AA46FE7A877E" box="[274,416,1821,1847]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" value="1921-05-16">16 mai 1921</date>
, per Jahandiez, dans le cratère du Djebel Hebbri, entre Azrou et Timhadit, dans les clairières des cédraires, sur basalte vers 
<quantity id="9402FFC5FFB1662CE79EAA1AFDEB8712" box="[474,561,1857,1883]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="m" value="1900.0">1900 m</quantity>
. Elle a été ensuite retrouvée par Maire dans les forêts de 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE2E8AA1AFAE08712" box="[1196,1338,1857,1883]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ilex">Quercus ilex</taxonomicName>
au dessus d’Azrou, sur calcaire jurassique vers 
<quantity id="9402FFC5FFB1662CE467AA3EFDA28736" box="[547,632,1893,1919]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" unit="m" value="1400.0">1400 m</quantity>
, en fruits plus que mûrs, le 
<date id="274474E0FFB1662CE5E1AA3EFB918736" box="[933,1099,1893,1920]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" value="1921-07-25">25 juillet 1921</date>
”. 
<typeStatus id="8C41EC82FFB1662CE21BAA3EFB418736" box="[1119,1179,1893,1919]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Type</typeStatus>
: 
<collectingCountry id="2BED12B0FFB1662CE2E0AA3EFAD68736" box="[1188,1292,1893,1919]" name="Morocco" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, Moyen 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE32DAA3EFA7D8736" box="[1385,1447,1893,1919]" class="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" family="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" genus="Atlas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Atlas</taxonomicName>
, above town Azrou, 1921, 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE7EDAAD1FCD587EA" box="[425,783,1929,1957]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">É. Jahandiez &amp;/or R. Maire s.n.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="53455220FFB1662FE6F9AAF6FD0E81D9" blockId="5.[136,1452,1281,2063]" lastBlockId="6.[136,1452,158,581]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="47" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
Note. Although the North African herbarium of the University of 
<collectingCountry id="2BED12B0FFB1662CE5F5AAF6FBDF878E" box="[945,1029,1965,1991]" name="Algeria" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Algeria</collectingCountry>
(AL) is listed in 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE295AAF6FA76878E" authority="Herbariorum" authorityName="Herbariorum" box="[1233,1452,1965,1991]" class="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" family="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" genus="Index" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mollusca (awaiting allocation)" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Index Herbariorum</taxonomicName>
online (sweetgum.nybg.org/science/ih/), no address or correspondents are given, and inquiry about the type collection of 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB1662CE6E2AAAEFEE08846" authorityName="Jahandiez &amp; Maire" authorityYear="1923" box="[166,314,2037,2063]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="josiae">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB1662CE6E2AAAEFEE08846" box="[166,314,2037,2063]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Arabis josiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was not possible. The original protologue (
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB1662CE55EAAAEFBF58846" author="Jahandiez, E. &amp; Maire, R." box="[794,1071,2037,2063]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="65 - 73" refId="ref6324" refString="Jahandiez, E. &amp; Maire, R. (1923) Plantae maroccanae novae. Bulletin de la Societe d'histoire naturelle de l'Afrique du Nord 14 (2): 65 - 73." type="journal article" year="1923">Jahandiez &amp; Maire 1923</bibRefCitation>
) lists two gatherings, and relevant 
<typeStatus id="8C41EC82FFB2662FE6CCADC4FF3080F0" box="[136,234,159,185]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">syntypes</typeStatus>
are available in MPU (with printed labels from AL “Université d’Algiere Herbier del’Afrique du Nord”) and AIX. The collections by Jahandiez were made on 
<date id="274474E0FFB2662FE4FCAD99FC948095" box="[696,846,194,221]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1921-05-16">16 May 1921</date>
(MPU-000159, AIX-000066) at 
<quantity id="9402FFC5FFB2662FE284AD99FACC8094" box="[1216,1302,194,221]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="1900.0">1900 m</quantity>
from 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB2662FE31EAD99FA718095" box="[1370,1451,194,220]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Cedrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE31EAD99FA718095" box="[1370,1451,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Cedrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forests, and they are immature plants in early stages of flowering. However, Maire’s collections (MPU-000157, MPU-000158) were made on 
<date id="274474E0FFB2662FE7D6AC51FDF9816D" box="[402,547,266,293]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1921-07-25">25 July 1921</date>
at 
<quantity id="9402FFC5FFB2662FE402AC51FD46816C" box="[582,668,266,293]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="1400.0">1400 m</quantity>
from 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB2662FE4A5AC50FCE5816C" box="[737,831,267,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE4A5AC50FCE5816C" box="[737,831,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forests. They are with fully mature plants. Because the original description includes flowering and fruiting material, and because the fruits are essential for the characterization of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB2662FE751AC09FEAD8125" authorityName="Al-Shehbaz, M. Koch, R. Karl, &amp; D. A. German" authorityYear="2022" box="[277,375,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hurkaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE751AC09FEAD8125" box="[277,375,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Hurkaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a designation of the specimen with mature fruits at AL as the 
<typeStatus id="8C41EC82FFB2662FE26FAC09FB488125" box="[1067,1170,338,364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">lectotype</typeStatus>
would be preferable, and its duplicate at MPU would then be the isolectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="53455220FFB2662FE6F9ACC0FAF7820C" blockId="6.[136,1452,158,581]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">
= 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB2662FE690ACC1FD8681FD" authority="Pau &amp; Font Quer" authorityName="Pau &amp; Font Quer" box="[212,604,410,437]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leptopoda">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE690ACC1FE4C81FD" box="[212,406,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Arabis leptopoda</emphasis>
Pau &amp; Font Quer
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB2662FE42EACC1FCFB81FD" author="Font Quer, P." box="[618,801,410,436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refId="ref5758" refString="Font Quer, P. (1928) Iter Maroccanum 1927. Exsiccata schedula. Natural Science Museum, Barcelona, 739 num." type="book" year="1928">Font Quer 1928</bibRefCitation>
: 
<superScript id="A48FFF68FFB2662FE568ACC0FC9881E1" attach="left" box="[812,834,410,437]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">no</superScript>
236, in sched.). ≡ 
<taxonomicName id="94FA29A3FFB2662FE256ACC0FE508191" authority="(Pau &amp; Font Quer) Pau &amp; Font Quer" authorityName="Pau &amp; Font Quer" baseAuthorityName="Pau &amp; Font Quer" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Arabis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="josiae" variety="leptopoda">
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE256ACC0FBAE81FD" box="[1042,1140,411,437]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">A. josiae</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE2EEACC1FAC081FD" box="[1194,1306,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">leptopoda</emphasis>
(Pau &amp; Font Quer) Pau &amp; Font Quer
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB2662FE7D2ACE5FD908191" author="Font Quer, P." box="[406,586,446,472]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" refId="ref5782" refString="Font Quer, P. (1929) Iter Maroccanum 1928. Exsiccata schedula. Natural Science Museum, Barcelona, 438 num." type="book" year="1929">Font Quer 1929</bibRefCitation>
: 
<superScript id="A48FFF68FFB2662FE417ACE4FDB38185" attach="left" box="[595,617,446,473]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">no</superScript>
139, in sched.). Type indication: “Hab. in saxosis, lacisque silvaticis montis Iguermalez (Atlante rhiphaeo), 
<quantity id="9402FFC5FFB2662FE7A1ACB9FDE181B4" box="[485,571,482,509]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="1950.0">1950 m</quantity>
. alt.; 7 junii”. 
<typeStatus id="8C41EC82FFB2662FE490ACB8FC9E81B4" box="[724,836,483,509]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Lectotype</typeStatus>
(designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="376B2FD1FFB2662FE5B6ACB9FB3D81B5" author="Nualart, N. &amp; Soriano, I. &amp; Perez Prieto, D. &amp; Ibanez, N." box="[1010,1255,482,508]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 94" refId="ref7952" refString="Nualart, N., Soriano, I., Perez Prieto, D. &amp; Ibanez, N. (2021) Catalogue and typification of the Moroccan taxa published by Carlos Pau. Phytotaxa 519 (1): 1 - 94. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 519.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Nualart 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE208ACB8FB5881B5" box="[1100,1154,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">et al.</emphasis>
2021: 14
</bibRefCitation>
):— 
<collectingCountry id="2BED12B0FFB2662FE354ACB9FA7281B5" box="[1296,1448,482,508]" name="Morocco" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">MOROCCO</collectingCountry>
: In saxosis, lacisque silvaticis montis Iguermalez (Atlante rhiphaeo), 
<quantity id="9402FFC5FFB2662FE5C2AF5DFC078268" box="[902,989,518,545]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.95" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" unit="m" value="1950.0">1950 m</quantity>
, 
<date id="274474E0FFB2662FE5ACAF5CFBA88269" box="[1000,1138,518,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="47" value="1928-06-07">7 June 1928</date>
, 
<emphasis id="618E8E32FFB2662FE239AF5CFABF8269" box="[1149,1381,518,545]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="47">Font Quer 236-1928</emphasis>
(MA-48513; isolectotypes BC-2978, BCN-17301, BM-000583666, GDA-28946, MPU-006331, MPU 006332).
</paragraph>
